definitions.definition: The Greek goddess of the dawn ; daughter of Hyperion and Theia , sister of Helios and Selene , wife of Astraeus ( god of the dusk ), and mother of the four Anemoi (" Winds "), and the five Astra Planeta (" Wandering Stars / Planets "). Her Roman counterpart is Aurora .

main_definition: ( Greek mythology ) The Greek goddess of the dawn ; daughter of Hyperion and Theia , sister of Helios and Selene , wife of Astraeus ( god of the dusk ), and mother of the four Anemoi (" Winds "), and the five Astra Planeta (" Wandering Stars / Planets "). Her Roman counterpart is Aurora .
